# Hypothesis portfolio

Queue of hypotheses that passed the entry gate. This is not a brainstorming
dump and not a permanent wish list.

Before adding a row, read `references/hypothesis_quality.md` and check whether
an existing row should be updated, merged, rejected, stale, or parked instead.

## Status legend

- `planned`: accepted into the queue, not yet running
- `in-progress`: currently being tested
- `supported-candidate`: result may support the claim, but promotion review has not run
- `supported`: promotion review passed; claim is warranted at stated scope
- `rejected`: contradicted or acceptance condition failed in an informative way
- `partial`: narrowed result; scope or condition must be named
- `merged`: duplicate / variant absorbed into another row
- `stale`: no longer relevant after later evidence or scope change
- `parked`: deferred with a named unblock condition
- `dropped`: failed entry gate or no longer worth testing

## Entries

| ID | Question / capability updated | Statement | Status | Success distinguishes | Failure distinguishes | Cannot distinguish | Linked state row | Next update |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| H1 | Q1 | [Falsifiable comparison statement.] | planned | [what becomes stronger] | [what becomes weaker / split] | [known ambiguity] | Q1 / E1 / C1 | YYYY-MM-DD |

## Rules

- Every hypothesis must update a row in `research_state.md`.
- Failure must teach something. If the failure column is empty, redesign.
- Parameter sweeps, threshold tweaks, and implementation variants usually do
  not become new hypotheses. Record them as robustness or engineering work.
- Do not keep a row active because effort was spent. Downgrade or retire it
  when the state changes.
